This paper discusses techniques for increasing the interpretability of machine learning models, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of designing user-friendly explanations, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the need for comprehensive evaluation metrics, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it relates to ensuring the transparency and accountability of machine learning models. Finally, the paper's focus on interpretability and transparency could also relate to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
